Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Contact and Convective Dryers Market

Contact and convective dryers market will reach at an estimated value of USD 245.37 million by 2028 and grow at a CAGR of 3.10% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Rise in the emerging adoption of superheated steam in convectional dryers acts as an essential factor driving the contact and convective dryers market.

Contact and convective dryers used to eradicate moisture and water content from various products, particularly heat-sensitive products, to progress the quality and durability of the end product.

Increase in the indispensable nature of contact & convective dryers in industrial processes is a crucial factor accelerating the market growth, also rise in the environmental concerns and stringent regulations to improve energy efficiency, rise in the research and development activities and increase in the demand from emerging economies are the major factors among others boosting the contact and convective dryers market. Moreover, increase in the technological advancements and modernization in the production techniques will further create new opportunities for contact and convective dryers market in the forecast period mentioned above.

However, rise in the cost of research and development activities in the market is the major factor among others restraining the market growth, and will further challenge the contact and convective dryers market in the forecast period mentioned above.

